commit.message:
Document ExceptHandler.name change

Fix #82

Optimize node constructors

For gast.Name construction without keyword parameters, this does 30%
faster than the previous implementation.

The new error message follows py3.12 convention.

Update unparser for py 3.12 and setup minimal testing

Finally fixes #79

Reflect AST changes to README

Related to #79

Support py 3.12 type parameters

Related to #79

Update CI configuration for python 3.12 (and 2.7!)

Related to #79

Support Type aliases from Python 3.12

Related to #79

Support TryStar from python 3.11

Fix #71
Support match statement from python 3.10
Add support for Python 3.11 and test 3.12-dev

Restore python2 testing and support

Fix #66

Support gast.unparse

This allows to remove the test dependency on astunparse, while adapting
CPython's astunparse to gast AST

Fix #64
Advertise version number

Test field count more accurately

Allow either 0 or #fields arguments, with #fields honoring keyword arguments

Support NamedExpr

Fix #58

Cleanup and optimize the way gast builds its AST

This gives a 5 to 10% speedup in ast generation depending on the input. As gast
relies on the tree generated by the ast module and does not create any sharing
with the original tree, we're slower, but that's what make it a clean and simple
module :-)
